cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and image processing, specifically on face recognition and synthesis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel architecture for the generative adversarial network, which involves training multiple networks to attend to local textures, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper introduces a combination of loss functions to constrain the ill-posed problem, which involves optimization and algorithmic techniques (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method on large pose face recognition, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques to achieve its results, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
